It was over.
I looked at the clock.
It was midnight past.
I looked at the older believers, whose Savior had not come, who were too proud to show their disappointment, who had believed too much and for too long to begin to doubt now.
But I was upset for them.
They had been deceived, deceived, embossed, and I had allowed myself to be taken with them.
