I talk to people I appreciate and others I don't like.
I speak to people I deeply disagree with.
But I always have some fantastic conversations with them.
For the next 10 minutes, I'd like to teach you how to talk and listen.
Many of you have already heard advice on this: looking people in the eye, thinking beforehand about interesting topics to talk about, looking at, nodding their heads and smiling to show your attention, repeating what you have heard or summarize it.
Forget all this.
